DHCP Dynamic Static Hosting Protocol
BOOTP Bootstrap Protocol

DHCP discover (broadcast), its looking for an IP address
DHCP offer (sending back confirm), 
DHCP request (accept request for that DHCP)
DHCP acknowledgement(agree to the DHCP sent)

DHCP server runs in your own broadcast domain

Quick review: 
    - Each broadcast domain must have only one DHCP server
    - Every modern OS comes with DHCP enabled by default
    - DHCP Relay enables a single DHCP server to service more than one broadcast domain
